    notes:
      "## The Three-Tier Semax Hierarchy\n\nThe catalog covers three related Semax compounds reflecting the molecule's evolution in research peptide use:\n\n**Base Semax:**\n- Original ACTH(4-7) Pro-Gly-Pro fragment\n- Plasma half-life ~20 minutes\n- Lower cost\n- Most extensively studied form in Russian pharmaceutical research (Russian product is base Semax)\n- More frequent dosing required for sustained effect\n- Best for users wanting original-form fidelity to Russian clinical research\n\n**N-Acetyl Semax Amidate (this entry):**\n- Stability-modified analog with N-acetyl + C-amide\n- Plasma half-life substantially extended (hours)\n- Most-used research peptide form\n- Practical dosing convenience\n- Best balance of cost / stability / efficacy for most research-protocol users\n\n**Adamax:**\n- Next-generation derivative with adamantane group at C-terminus\n- Most potent and longest-acting\n- Premium pricing\n- Stronger BDNF response in preclinical data\n- Best for users wanting maximum potency or running protocols where dosing frequency is constraining\n\n**Decision frame:**\n- **Cost-conscious / Russian research fidelity:** base Semax\n- **Practical research-protocol use (most users):** N-Acetyl Semax Amidate (this entry)\n- **Premium / maximum potency:** Adamax\n\n## Beginner Protocol\n200mcg IM or subQ × first dose AM to assess tolerance and effect profile. If well-tolerated, advance to 300mcg/dose AM × 2 days, then 2 days off, then 2 days on, etc. **Strict AM dosing.** Track: cognitive function (focus, motivation, processing speed), mood, sleep quality (the central tolerability metric), energy. Effects often perceptible within 30-60 minutes of injection.\n\n## Advanced Protocol — Canonical Real-World Example\n\n**The IM protocol (one experienced user's actual cycling pattern):**\n- **30mg vial reconstituted with 3ml bacteriostatic water** = 10mg/ml working concentration\n- **0.3mg per dose IM** = 0.03ml per injection (insulin syringe required for this small volume)\n- **AM dosing only** — strict timing\n- **2 days on / 2 days off cycling** — sustained protocol use without cumulative sleep debt\n- **Rationale for cycling:** continuous daily use produces 4.5-hour-night sleep disruption that is unsustainable for weeks; 2-on/2-off allows long-running protocols (months) without sleep debt accumulation\n- **Rationale for IM (vs subQ or intranasal):** consistent absorption profile, avoidance of intranasal mucosal irritation with sustained use, established personal tolerance\n\nThis pattern represents a real-world advanced-user adaptation balancing efficacy with tolerability. Other route choices (subQ, intranasal) work; the cycling pattern is what allows sustained protocol use.\n\n**Comprehensive nootropic stack:** N-Acetyl Semax Amidate 300mcg AM cycled 2-on/2-off + Lion's Mane 1000mg/day continuous (NGF/BDNF complementarity) + Alpha-GPC 600mg/day continuous (cholinergic substrate) + Bacopa Monnieri 300mg/day continuous + omega-3 high-DHA 2g/day + B-complex methylated. The Semax pulse-cycle layered onto continuous nootropic foundation provides peak cognitive enhancement during on-cycle days and sustained baseline support continuously.\n\n**Russian classical Selank+Semax pairing:** N-Acetyl Semax Amidate 300mcg AM (cognitive enhancement, focus, motivation) + N-Acetyl Selank Amidate 300mcg AM or PM (anxiety modulation, calm). The pairing addresses cognitive performance + anxiety simultaneously — neither compound alone provides the dual effect, and the combination is the classical Russian protocol approach.\n\n**Stroke recovery / TBI adjunct (under neurologist coordination):** N-Acetyl Semax Amidate as adjunct to standard rehabilitation; coordinate with neurologist; the Russian clinical pharmaceutical use establishes the rationale.\n\n## Sleep Disruption — The Central Tolerability Reality\n\nMost discussions of Semax in nootropic communities understate the sleep impact. Real-world experience from sustained users converges on a consistent pattern:\n\n- Continuous daily Semax (>3-4 consecutive days) produces meaningful sleep disruption for most users\n- Sleep onset difficulty, early awakening, reduced total sleep are typical\n- The cumulative sleep debt becomes unsustainable within ~1-2 weeks of daily use\n- Cycling (2-on/2-off, or 3-on/4-off, or similar patterns) allows sleep recovery on off-days\n- Strict AM dosing (vs evening) substantially reduces same-day sleep impact but doesn't eliminate cumulative effect with daily use\n\nFor users encountering Semax for the first time: respect the sleep impact. Don't run weeks of continuous daily dosing expecting it to be sustainable — it isn't for most people. The cycling protocol isn't optional efficacy maintenance; it's tolerability requirement.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\n30mg lyophilized vial; reconstitute with 3ml bacteriostatic water → 10mg/ml working concentration (0.1ml = 1mg = 1000mcg; 0.03ml = 300mcg). Insulin syringe required for accurate small-volume dosing. Sites: IM (deltoid, gluteus, quadriceps), subQ (abdominal, thigh), or intranasal spray (different reconstitution dilution typical for nasal). Refrigerate reconstituted product; use within 28–30 days.\n\n## Synergies\n**N-Acetyl Selank Amidate:** the classical Russian cognitive+calm pairing. **Lion's Mane:** complementary NGF/BDNF mechanism. **Alpha-GPC / CDP-Choline:** cholinergic substrate; supports the cholinergic activity Semax modulates. **Bromantane:** complementary actoprotector mechanism; together provide cognitive + physical performance under stress. **Bacopa Monnieri:** complementary cognitive mechanism. **Magnesium glycinate:** counters Semax-induced insomnia at night (PM dosing of magnesium glycinate is essentially mandatory for Semax users). **Omega-3 high-DHA:** foundational neuroprotection and BDNF support.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nRussian clinical research base for base Semax (Mjasoedov 1992, Skvortsova 2013 for stroke recovery). The N-Acetyl Amidate analog has less direct clinical trial evidence — research peptide use ahead of formal RCT validation for the analog form specifically. The mechanism is well-characterized at the molecular level; the modifications extend duration without changing fundamental mechanism.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMechanism well-characterized — BDNF/NGF upregulation is one of the better-established cognitive enhancement mechanisms among research peptides. Russian pharmaceutical regulatory backing for base Semax establishes safety and efficacy in pharmaceutical-grade contexts. The N-Acetyl Amidate analog has less direct clinical evidence than base Semax but mechanism extrapolates. Long real-world research community use establishes general tolerability patterns including the sleep disruption reality.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: solid mechanistic foundation (BDNF/NGF upregulation; TrkB sensitization; HGF/c-Met activation); Russian pharmaceutical evidence base for base Semax; mechanistic extrapolation supports the amidate analog. Anecdote: extensive nootropic community use; subjective effects often perceptible within 30-60 minutes; sleep disruption with continuous daily use is the consistent real-world finding requiring cycling adaptation. Decision frame: foundational nootropic peptide for cognitive enhancement / focus / motivation / mood elevation; the IM/subQ/intranasal route choice is user preference; cycling 2-on/2-off is practical tolerability adaptation; pairs with N-Acetyl Selank Amidate for classical Russian cognitive+calm protocol; sleep impact is real and warrants respect for sustained use.",
