    notes:
      "## Bemethyl + Bromantane — The Classical Actoprotector Pairing\n\nBemethyl and Bromantane are the two prototype actoprotectors in the Russian-defined drug class, with complementary mechanisms:\n\n**Bromantane mechanisms:**\n- Dopaminergic enhancement via tyrosine hydroxylase activation\n- Serotonergic modulation\n- Hypoxia tolerance\n- Mood elevation, motivation\n\n**Bemethyl mechanisms:**\n- Enhanced gluconeogenesis under stress\n- Protein synthesis enhancement\n- Antihypoxic effects (more pronounced than Bromantane)\n- Mitochondrial substrate utilization\n- Recovery from exhaustion\n\n**The pairing rationale:** Bromantane addresses CNS-mediated performance enhancement (motivation, focus, drive); Bemethyl addresses biochemical-substrate performance enhancement (energy metabolism, protein synthesis, oxygen utilization). The combination provides comprehensive actoprotector class coverage — neither compound alone addresses both CNS and biochemical mechanisms.\n\n**Classical Russian protocol:** Bromantane 50-100mg AM + Bemethyl 250mg BID (AM and noon, avoiding PM) — both cycled, often 4-on/2-off matching pattern. Used historically in Russian Olympic training, military operations, cosmonaut training, and chronic fatigue / asthenia clinical contexts.\n\n## Beginner Protocol\n125-250mg AM × first dose to assess tolerance. If well-tolerated, advance to 250mg BID (AM and noon) × 5 days, 2 days off, repeat. Track: physical performance (exercise tolerance, recovery), cognitive performance under fatigue, sleep quality, cardiovascular response (HR, palpitations).\n\n## Advanced Protocol\n**Comprehensive actoprotector class stack:** Bemethyl 250mg BID + Bromantane 50-100mg AM, both cycled 4-on/2-off. The classical Russian actoprotector pairing for users wanting comprehensive stress-resilience and physical/cognitive performance under sustained demand.\n\n**Comprehensive nootropic stack with Bemethyl:** Bemethyl 250mg BID cycled + N-Acetyl Semax Amidate 300mcg AM cycled 2-on/2-off + Lion's Mane 1000mg/day continuous + Alpha-GPC 600mg/day continuous + magnesium glycinate 400mg PM (counters any cumulative sleep disruption). The multi-mechanism approach addresses CNS cognitive enhancement (Semax), biochemical performance enhancement (Bemethyl), and continuous nootropic foundation (Lion's Mane + Alpha-GPC).\n\n**Asthenic / chronic fatigue protocol (under prescriber coordination):** Bemethyl as adjunct in chronic fatigue / post-viral asthenia / adjustment disorder contexts — the Russian clinical pharmaceutical use case. Often paired with Bromantane and/or N-Acetyl Selank Amidate for comprehensive recovery support.\n\n**Athletic / training context:** Bemethyl as recovery / adaptation support during high-volume training periods. Cycled to prevent tolerance; AM/noon dosing only to avoid sleep impact. Useful for users undergoing sustained training stress where energy substrate availability and tissue recovery become limiting.\n\n## The Cardiovascular Ceiling — Same Pattern as Bromantane\n\nLike Bromantane, Bemethyl's actoprotector classification ('not classical stimulant cardiovascular profile') is true at standard doses but has limits:\n\n- At 750mg+ daily, palpitations occur in some users — first-person dose-ceiling signal\n- Cardiovascular caution at higher doses is real for sensitive users\n- The standard 250mg BID (500mg/day) dose is well-tolerated for most users\n- Combining Bemethyl + Bromantane at high doses of both compounds can amplify cardiovascular load\n\nFor users running paired Bemethyl + Bromantane: keep both at moderate doses rather than pushing both to upper end simultaneously. Standard doses (Bemethyl 250mg BID + Bromantane 50-100mg AM) are well-tolerated for most users; aggressive dosing of both produces cumulative cardiovascular load.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\nN/A — oral capsule or tablet. AM and noon dosing typical; avoid PM dosing. With or without food acceptable.\n\n## Synergies\n**Bromantane:** complementary actoprotector (biochemical + CNS mechanism pairing). **N-Acetyl Semax Amidate:** complementary cognitive enhancement via different mechanism. **Lion's Mane:** complementary cognitive mechanism. **Alpha-GPC / CDP-Choline:** cholinergic substrate. **Magnesium glycinate:** counters any sleep disruption with PM dosing. **Mitochondrial pillar (SS-31, MOTS-C, Humanin, PQQ, CoQ10):** complementary mitochondrial function support; the multi-mechanism approach addresses different aspects of mitochondrial homeostasis.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nRussian clinical research base — Smirnov 2003 (athletic performance), Bobkov 1984 (foundational characterization), multiple Russian-language papers in asthenia, hypoxia tolerance, recovery contexts. The Russian clinical evidence is substantial; English-language Western RCT evidence limited.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMechanism partially characterized — gluconeogenesis enhancement, antihypoxic effects, and protein synthesis enhancement are documented; the actoprotector class concept is Russian-defined. Russian clinical use establishes pharmaceutical-grade safety and efficacy in specific clinical contexts. Long real-world use in Russian medical practice (~30 years) provides general safety baseline. The cardiovascular dose-ceiling is real-world established.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: substantial Russian clinical use base; mechanism partially characterized; English-language RCT evidence limited. Anecdote: extensive use in nootropic and biohacking communities (less prominent than Bromantane); subjective effects often perceptible within hours; dose-ceiling cardiovascular effects (palpitations at 750mg+) are consistent first-person finding worth respecting; less sleep disruption than Bromantane / Semax for most users. Decision frame: Russian-pharmaceutical-class actoprotector with distinguishing antihypoxic and gluconeogenesis-enhancing mechanisms; pairs with Bromantane in classical actoprotector pattern; cycling discipline matters; cardiovascular dose-ceiling real at higher doses; useful component of comprehensive nootropic / recovery / athletic stacks.",
